RHS_PREGNANCY_BODY = <<eof
<p>
Pregnancy can be a confusing and wonderful time in life. It may also be the first interaction you’ve had dealing with the health insurance company, coordinating so many medical appointments, and making daily decisions that impact another human being. There’s a sea of information out there. We’re here to give you peace of mind, get you organized, and make sure you and your baby are happy and healthy.
</p>
<strong>
Your Timing, Your Needs
</strong>
<p>
No matter where you are in your pregnancy, your Personal Health Assistant (PHA) will create a personalized experience for you and your baby.
</p>
<p>
What to expect throughout your pregnancy:
</p>
<ul>
<li>
<img src="/assets/icon_checkin.png">
<span>
Weekly check-ins
</span>
</li>
<li>
<img src="/assets/icon_plan.png">
<span>
A personalized plan just for your pregnancy
</span>
</li>
<li>
<img src="/assets/icon_appt.png">
<span>
Appointment preparation and follow up
</span>
</li>
<li>
<img src="/assets/icon_recommendations.png">
<span>
Recommendations for the best products, classes, and services in your area
</span>
</li>
<li>
<img src="/assets/nurseline.png">
<span>
Access to expert Mayo Clinic nurses any time of day or night
</span>
</li>
</ul>
<p>
Open the sections below to get more details about trimester-specific services.
</p>
<div class="section-head closed" data-section-id="0">
First Trimester
</div>
<div class="section disabled" id="section-0">
<p>
It’s just the beginning. Your PHA will help you get organized by:
</p>
<ul>
<li>
Finding great doctors, midwives, and nutritionists to build your Care Team,
</li>
<li>
Getting you ready for your first prenatal appointments,
</li>
<li>
Setting up a baby budget,
</li>
<li>
Providing customized nutrition guidance,
</li>
<li>
Clarifying your insurance coverage,
</li>
<li>
Screening for risk factors,
</li>
<li>
And helping you manage symptoms, if you’re having them.
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="section-head closed" data-section-id="1">
Second Trimester
</div>
<div class="section disabled" id="section-1">
<p>
You’re over the first hurdle. Your PHA will help you focus on your health and well being by:
</p>
<ul>
<li>
Choosing a birth place that fits your needs,
</li>
<li>
Finding a birth place,
</li>
<li>
Selecting a childbirth and parenting class,
</li>
<li>
Making a plan to help you stay active,
</li>
<li>
Crafting meal plans,
</li>
<li>
And helping you manage and reduce complications of high risk pregnancy
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="section-head closed last" data-section-id="2">
Third Trimester
</div>
<div class="section disabled last" id="section-2">
<p>
You’re almost there. Your PHA will help you take care of all the final details to plan for the kind of birth that you want by:
</p>
<ul>
<li>
Creating a birth plan,
</li>
<li>
Helping add your baby to your insurance,
</li>
<li>
Finding lactation specialists,
</li>
<li>
Signing you up for right childbirth preparation class,
</li>
<li>
Finding you a doula,
</li>
<li>
Choosing the best baby products for your needs,
</li>
<li>
Helping you decide on birthing options like cord-blood banking or placenta preservation,
</li>
<li>
And vetting products like breast pumps and baby carriers.
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<p>
<strong>
Building a Relationship
</strong>
</p>
<p>
After your baby is born, your PHA will continue to support you and your child’s needs, like finding a highly-rated pediatrician, starting a feeding schedule and helping you make decisions about early medical care. With your PHA you’ll always be prepared for all the unexpected things that come up along the way. We’re here for you and your family as you make this transition into motherhood.
</p>
eof
